### B. System Architecture
- How Next.js App Router replaces a separate Express/FastAPI backend (Route Handlers as API layer)
- The route group architecture: `(public)`, `(student)`, `(teacher)`, `(employee)` — each with their own layout
- How `src/middleware.ts` acts as the gateway — edge-level RBAC that never hits the DB
- Why all 35 models live in `src/models/` and how the Mongoose global cache in `db.ts` prevents connection pool exhaustion on Vercel's serverless functions
- The Cloudinary integration for media (images, PDFs, DOCX uploads)
- State management: React local state + Server Actions + fetch-based SWR-like patterns (no Redux/Zustand)
- Framer Motion integration for UX polish (staggered lists, AnimatePresence)

