### H. How I Would Improve It Further

**Each improvement must address a real gap visible in the codebase:**

1. **Redis-backed rate limiter** — current in-memory limiter (`rateLimit.ts`) doesn't share state across Vercel function instances. Redis (Upstash) would make it globally consistent.
2. **MongoDB Atlas Search** — full-text search on `Program.name`, `LibraryDocument.title`, `Notice.title` is currently missing. Atlas Search with `$search` aggregation stage would enable instant search.
3. **Background job queue** — auto-fee creation (`autoCreateStudentFee.ts`) runs inline in the approval API. A queue (BullMQ or Vercel Cron) would decouple this.
4. **Caching layer** — public APIs (`/api/public/courses`, `/api/public/notices`) are fetched fresh on every request. ISR (Incremental Static Regeneration) or `revalidate: 3600` on Server Components would eliminate DB calls for read-heavy public pages.
5. **Multi-language support** — the `CollegeSettings` model and public pages are English-only. Adding `i18n` with `next-intl` and a Hindi locale would serve the actual Ayurveda audience.
6. **Soft delete on more models** — currently only `LibraryDocument` has `is_deleted`. Other models use hard deletes. Implementing soft delete across `Notice`, `JobPosting`, `Result` would improve recoverability.
7. **WebSocket/SSE notifications** — the current `NotificationSchema` is polling-based. Server-Sent Events or WebSocket (via Ably/Pusher) would give real-time notice delivery.
8. **ChatPDF / AI integration** — the library already stores Ayurveda textbooks in Cloudinary. An LLM layer (RAG via LangChain) over `LibraryDocument` content would be a natural next step.

